{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Amy Lane | nickname = The Meadow | country = England | image = | location = [[Chesham]], [[Buckinghamshire]] | establishment = 1907 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year2 = 1978 | club2 = [[Minor Counties East]] | year1 = <small>1907, 1951-1982 & 1993</small> | club1 = [[Buckinghamshire County Cricket Club|Buckinghamshire]] | date = 22 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/405.html Ground profile }}
[[File:AmyLane1.jpg|thumb|The pavilion at Amy Lane]]
'''Amy Lane''', also known as '''The Meadow''', is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Chesham]], [[Buckinghamshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1907, [[Buckinghamshire County Cricket Club|Buckinghamshire]] played the [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire Second XI]]. Buckinghamshire next used the ground in 1951, and from 1951 to 1982 the ground hosted 32 Minor Counties Championship matches, the last of which saw Buckinghamshire play [[Suffolk County Cricket Club|Suffolk]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/405_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Amy Lane]</ref> Buckinghamshire returned to the ground in 1993 to play the first and only [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] match held at the ground, against [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/405_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on Amy Lane]</ref>
The ground has also held 2 [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches. The first was between Buckinghamshire and [[Hampshire County Cricket Club|Hampshire]] in 2nd round of the [[1970 Gillette Cup]]. A [[Minor Counties East]] team played [[Leicestershire County Cricket Club|Leicestershire]] in the 1978 [[Benson and Hedges Cup]], which was the final List-A match held on the ground.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/405_a.html List-A Matches played on Amy Lane]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of Chesham Cricket Club.<ref>[http://www.cheshamcc.co.uk/ Chesham Cricket Club]</ref>
