{{Infobox stadium | name = Arsenal Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Arsenal Stadium in Tula.jpg | image_size = 275 | caption = Stadium in 2014 | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Tula, Russia|Tula]], [[Russia]] | coordinates = {{Coord|54|10|28.5|N|37|36|9.8|E|display=inline,title|type:landmark}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|1959|08|29}} | renovated = 1996–1998, 2014 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | surface = grass | capacity = 20,048 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[FC Arsenal Tula]] (1959–present) | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} The '''Arsenal Stadium''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Tula, Russia|Tula]], [[Russia]]. It is used mostly for [[FC Arsenal Tula]] [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium was constructed in 1959 and holds 20,048 people<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/russia.shtml |title=Stadiums in Russia |publisher=World Stadiums |date= |accessdate=2012-06-02}}</ref>
