The '''[[Australian Institute of Sport]] (AIS)''' competed in the [[Women's National Basketball League]] ([[Women's National Basketball League|WNBL]]) as a team of the AIS Athletes. They won the WNBL Championship just once, in the [[1998–99 WNBL season]], led by a young [[Lauren Jackson]]. The team continued to compete in the WNBL through the [[2011–12 WNBL season|2011–12 season]], but withdrew at the end of that season. AIS were largely uncompetitive in their last years in the WNBL, winning only 29 matches and losing 188 in their final ten WNBL seasons, including a two-season record of 1—41 in [[2005–06 WNBL season|2005–06]] and [[2006–07 WNBL season|2006–07]]. The withdrawal was coordinated with [[Basketball Australia]], which sought to address the flagging depth in its female junior ranks.<ref>{{cite web|author=Jon Tuxworth |url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/sport/basketball/ais-set-to-exit-wnbl-20120423-1xhpj.html |title=AIS set to exit WNBL |publisher=Canberratimes.com.au |date=2012-04-24 |accessdate=2012-09-12}}</ref>

