The '''Best Angler [[ESPY Award]]''' has been presented annually since [[2006 in sports|2006]] to the [[amateur sports|amateur]] or [[professional sports|professional]] [[angling]] [[sport fishing|sport fisherman]], irrespective of gender or nationality, adjudged to be the best in a given [[calendar year]]; although the award may technically be presented to an angler of any [[fish]], in practice only [[bass fishing|bass fishermen]] are considered as nominees.
[[Voting|Balloting]] for the award is undertaken by [[fan (aficionado)|fan]]s over the [[Internet]] from amongst between three and five choices selected by the ESPN Select Nominating Committee, and the award is conferred in June to reflect performance and achievement over the preceding twelve months.
