{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=June 2018}} {{Refimprove|date=August 2016}} {{Coord|12.98824|N|80.22641|E|display=title}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Indian Institute of Technology Chemplast Ground | nickname = Chemplast Ground | country = India | image = | location = [[IIT Madras]], [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]] | establishment = 1998 | seating_capacity = n/a | end1 = | end2 = | club1 = [[Tamil Nadu cricket team]] | year1 = 1998-present | date = 22 August | year = 2015 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/58005.html Ground profile }} '''Chemplast Cricket Ground''' or '''Indian Institute of Technology Chemplast Ground''' is a cricket ground in the [[IIT Madras]] campus. The ground is an important cricket venue<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/society/pitching-for-cricket/article29860.ece Pitching for cricket]</ref> and is described by cricketer [[Sachin Tendulkar]] as the most scenic in the country{{citation needed|date=October 2014}}. It is set amongst greenery.
The ground has hosted eight [[Women's cricket]] [[One Day International|ODI]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/959_wo.html Women's ODI]</ref> The first match record at ground was in 2003 [[India women's national cricket team|India Women's]] and [[New Zealand women's national cricket team|New Zealand Women's]]<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/78/78571.html Scoredcard]</ref>
