{{New Zealand NBL Awards}} The '''National Basketball League Kiwi MVP''' is an annual [[National Basketball League (New Zealand)|National Basketball League]] (NBL) award given since the [[1984 New Zealand NBL season]] to the best performing New Zealand player(s) of the regular season. With no MVP award given for the league's first two seasons, in 1984, the league named its first MVP in New Zealander John "Dutchie" Rademakers. The award then went on a six-year hiatus before being brought back in [[1991 New Zealand NBL season|1991]]. However, the league did not recognise imports, with only New Zealanders being able to win MVP honours. That was until [[2003 New Zealand NBL season|2003]] when a [[New Zealand NBL Most Valuable Player Award|league-wide MVP award]] was introduced alongside the Kiwi MVP to allow imports the opportunity to win.<ref>{{cite web|title=2015 Bartercard NBL Handbook|work=Basketball.org.nz|url=http://www.basketball.org.nz/Portals/26/2015%20Bartercard%20National%20Basketball%20League%20Handbook.pdf|accessdate=3 November 2015|page=28–34}}</ref>
