'''''Puli Bidda''''' ([[Indian English|translation]]:Son of the Tiger) is a 1981 [[Telugu film|Telugu]] [[Sports film|sports]] [[drama film]] directed by [[V. Madhusudhan Rao]] and produced by N. Seshagiri Rao under Heramba Chitra Mandir. The film stars [[Krishnam Raju]] and [[Sridevi]] in the lead roles. 
It is a remake of the 1978 Kannada film ''[[Thayige Thakka Maga]]'',  starring Dr. Rajkumar and Padmapriya, which was also remade in Hindi as ''[[Main Intequam Loonga]]'' (1982), starring [[Dharmendra]] and [[Reena Roy]].
The soundtrack was composed by [[K. Chakravarthy|Chakravarthy]]. Krishnam Raju acted as a [[boxer]] in the film. 

