{{infobox country at games | NPC = USA | NPCname = [[United States Paralympic Committee]] | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1988 | flagcaption = [[Flag of the United States]] | oldcode = | website = {{url|www.teamusa.org/US-Paralympics }} | location = [[Seoul]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = 1 | gold = 92 | silver = 90 | bronze = 91 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''The [[United States]]''' sent a delegation to compete at the '''[[1988 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Seoul]], [[South Korea]]. Its athletes finished first in the gold and overall medal count.<ref name="medaltable">{{cite web| url=http://www.paralympic.org/release/Main_Sections_Menu/Sports/Results/paralympics_reports.html?type=medalstandings&games=1988PG| title=Medal Standings Seoul 1988 Paralympic Games |publisher=''International Paralympic Committee''|accessdate=2009-08-05|year=1988}}</ref>
